<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="57" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,212]" pageId="6" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,152,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="57">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the very prolonged head posterior to the eyes, resembling a very long giraffe-like neck. This is a unique feature within the Clavigeritae.
</paragraph>
